              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1793053049910820271">I&apos;m giving this 5 as it was a nice sweet romantic story. Theo and Lucys&apos; relationship blossoms and develops over a period of 12 months so everything makes sense and nothing about their relationship was forced as they went from Personal trainer and client, to friends, to lovers.<br/><br/>In brief, Lucy works for an advertising agency and after hitting on the marketing idea of loosing weight, getting fit and at the same time promoting Palm Club gym she meets up with Theo-dorable a good looking, kind guy who</span>
  <span id="freeText1793053049910820271" style="display:none">I'm giving this 5 as it was a nice sweet romantic story. Theo and Lucys' relationship blossoms and develops over a period of 12 months so everything makes sense and nothing about their relationship was forced as they went from Personal trainer and client, to friends, to lovers.<br /><br />In brief, Lucy works for an advertising agency and after hitting on the marketing idea of loosing weight, getting fit and at the same time promoting Palm Club gym she meets up with Theo-dorable a good looking, kind guy who's not really who Lucy thinks he is......there's alot more to Theo than meets the eye. As Lucy progresses with her training regime Theo works his way into her heart but Lucy has a secret so she's kind of wary of Theo and wanting to fall in love with him all at the same time. As Time goes on Lucy falls hard and deep for Theo for whom the feeling is recipricated. Theres some 'misunderstandings' to liven the tale up and a lovely HEA plus some super secondary characters who are all just wonderful, so if you're looking for a nice romance with no angst this may well be for you:) </span>
