        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="ebook 9781429903776" href="/book/show/7468928-he-loves-lucy">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2505272-flibbityfloob?shelf=contemporary">contemporary</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2505272-flibbityfloob?shelf=witty-i-am-not">witty-i-am-not</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2505272-flibbityfloob?shelf=read-in-2010">read-in-2010</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2505272-flibbityfloob?shelf=chick-lit">chick-lit</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2505272-flibbityfloob?shelf=zaftig-heroine">zaftig-heroine</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer69605959" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1150146821166321491">I had a lot of mixed feelings about this one. On one hand, I loved the character of Theo and his flirty behavior when motivating Lucy. On the other hand, I found the entire story to be very unrealistic. Lucy was losing weight way too fast, and I missed some of the realism that could come with the tale. Yes, I wanted a happy ending, but I wanted a more realistic one. It was a bit too sappy for me in the end. I think it would have been cool if she stalled at 165 pounds or something like that...</span>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

